  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Livelihoods of Refugee and Host Communities in Bassikounou, Hodh Ech Chargui IV</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project contributes to the empowerment of refugees excluded from direct assistance in Mauritania. In particular, IOM aims to support them through the development of economic activities, and improvement of economic capacities of host communities with adequate support for their resilience and integration in the decision-making process of their community. Through this project, IOM is also supporting the Government in the implementation of its national strategy to combat the spread of the COVID-19 epidemic by carrying out some activities to strengthen the prevention of the spread of COVID-19 among refugees and host communities. Particular attention is being paid to inclusion of gender considerations in the project needs analysis, design, implementation, monitoring and evaluation to enhance relevance and impact of the action for the targeted communities.</narrative>
  </description>
